<br>
What is so wrong with them soloing for good exp?  Many classes kite their way through the levels.  Some root / dot mobs that don't summon.  It just happens that charm is very quick, which I think should probably be changed, but nothing drastic.  Maybe take 50% exp, but only when the chanter is ungrouped.  Don't forget that often these chanters die multiple times per night, and have to get a good amount of aa to make it even somewhat reliable.<br>
<br>
Charm wasn't the problem, some situations were, now they are taking away a part of the enchanter class if they go through with this. <p>Veteran Overdorf <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18306">Hussar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Kneeslicer - Drunken Tsunami</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=smohg>Smohg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/03 1:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2002.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: haha</span><hr size=1> pfft - that's bullsh*t - I charmed mobs with my enchanter to lvl 50 (from about lvl 30) and let me tell you that not many enchanters did that because guess why - its hard. Its hard like you dont get much better experience than when you are in a group type hard - and frequently you get worse. Now you got enchanters that instead of making an AA in 3-4 hours are making it in 30 mins. I notice some are just getting twinks and having them grouped and sitting whilethey PL the crap out of their twinks. Experience is SO good you can take the 50% exp penalty, take a penatly for having another class grouped and just sitting there, and STILL make more exp on both than you can playing the game as intended. Why verant made it so freaking easy is beyond me (developers play enchanters??) - its like giving warriors 99% damage mitigation or something.<br>
