yers, be fairly easily controlled, and kick out the damage of 2 to 3 full groups.  It's broken, plain and simple.  Everyone playing PoP who gives a damn about class balance has known it for a long time.  A friend of mine plays a chanter and he laughs about how crazy powerful it is on a regular basis.  Another friend plays a mage and really gets a kick out of how pathetically easy BoT is for him.  If done right, it's not even very risky.  As for soloability after a nerf, tough crap... these are the freaking gods' realms.  You shouldn't be able to solo in tier3, period, end of story and IMO not in tier2 either.  There are plenty of older zones where people can solo all they want.  wahhh... the exp isn't as good as tier2+ PoP.  Too bad.  That's the price one pays for not getting a group.  A group should be more effective in getting both exp and loot and the opposite is true with charm.  Soloing is far, far better exp than getting a group when you're charming and in some cases allows for getting loot that would normally take a group or more too.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaldanm>kaldanm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/03 4:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2002.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pubkal.free.fr/images/clan.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters and Druids... Charming</span><hr size=1> Chanter could still use charm :<br>
